# Project documentation

## What to maintain

- **`docs/`** — project documentation: what the system is, how it is structured, how to use it.
- **`README.md`** — short entry point; link into `docs/`, do not duplicate long content.

## What not to put in `docs/`

- Development journals, session notes, or chronological change logs.
- Agent-only commentary; write for anyone reading the repo.

## When to update

When you add, remove, or change **behavior, public API, or architectural intent**, update the relevant doc in the same change:

| Area | File |
|------|------|
| Solution, goals, conventions | `docs/overview.md` |
| Character, drives, factory | `docs/character.md` |

Add a new `docs/*.md` topic file when a subsystem is large enough to deserve its own page; add a row to the table in `docs/README.md`.

## Style

- Present tense, descriptive (how things work now).
- Prefer links to source paths over copying large APIs.
- Keep pages focused; split rather than one growing file.
